{
  "doc_id": "8141",
  "text": "Garlic (Allium sativum L.) is native to Western and Central Asia, and it has been cultivated and consumed extensively for centuries because of its medicinal and edible value [CITATION_1] . The various biological activities of garlic extract include antioxidant, anticancer, antihypertensive, and age-resisting activities, and they have attracted increasing interest [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Additionally, processed garlic products in the domestic seasoning market, including fried garlic oil, have been applied in a variety of food products, such as chips, breads, and instant noodles, as a flavor ingredient. Accordingly, the use of fried garlic oil has been progressively increasing due to demand in the food manufacturing industry.",
